00:19:59,896 --> 00:20:00,977
So I am an attorney.

266
00:20:01,337 --> 00:20:06,980
I have spent some time studying various aspects of the legal issues here, so land use and

267
00:20:08,074 --> 00:20:12,780
and zoning and municipal law that would be related to a discussion on zoning.

268
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:15,423
So I do have a little bit on that.

269
00:20:16,024 --> 00:20:18,647
Of course, you know, you always say to yourself, you know, I'm not this and I'm not that.

270
00:20:18,687 --> 00:20:20,830
So I'm not an engineer or an economist.

271
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:26,096
So giving you my kind of legal take on things so far is also just as an informed citizen.

272
00:20:27,578 --> 00:20:29,359
who's interested in these politics.

273
00:20:30,559 --> 00:20:48,184
So as you mentioned, zoning resumed in January, very much a result of the election outcome, I would say, in terms of the pacing and the process, but also due to just the logistics of getting more funding to pay our zoning consultant to get it going again.

274
00:20:48,885 --> 00:20:55,527
So that was done and the City Council and Community Development Board decided that they would start with Medford Square.

