The city believes and elected leadership believes this will be consistent with its affordable housing goals.

377
00:28:53,464 --> 00:28:57,748
But ultimately, you know, you have to look at the facts in terms of what is being proposed.

378
00:28:58,548 --> 00:29:01,110
to determine whether or not it will achieve any sort of policy goal.

379
00:29:01,250 --> 00:29:04,692
So I'll just give you some numbers on that.

380
00:29:04,712 --> 00:29:07,254
283 new apartments, that's the plan.

381
00:29:08,015 --> 00:29:11,537
About 56% of them would be intended to be affordable.

382
00:29:11,677 --> 00:29:15,740
You can see in this diagram here a map from the developer.

383
00:29:16,761 --> 00:29:19,683
You'll notice, I find this amusing, and the developer is aware of it.

384
00:29:20,023 --> 00:29:22,005
Notice Lakeview Avenue on that map.

385
00:29:22,745 --> 00:29:23,406
doesn't exist.

386
00:29:23,666 --> 00:29:25,367
No, there is no Lakeview.

387
00:29:25,627 --> 00:29:26,508
That's Riverside Avenue.

388
00:29:26,548 --> 00:29:27,568
Yeah, Riverside.

389
00:29:28,249 --> 00:29:33,152
So maybe they're going to change it to Lakeview because, you know, or Riverview it should be, not Lakeview.

390
00:29:33,212 --> 00:29:34,833
Maybe, but I think it was just an error.

391
00:29:35,253 --> 00:29:36,554
Yeah, obviously.

392
00:29:36,855 --> 00:29:38,916
Not to, yeah, it's not the most important thing.

393
00:29:38,996 --> 00:29:39,636
No, I know.

394
00:29:39,656 --> 00:29:43,039
People do make mistakes, but pointing that out there in case people are confused.

395
00:29:43,059 --> 00:29:43,199
Yeah.

396
00:29:43,559 --> 00:29:46,421
But yeah, about 56% affordable, what does that mean?

397
00:29:47,701 --> 00:29:49,102
80% median area income.

398
00:29:50,002 --> 00:30:00,308
My understanding of this median area income is it's a state calculation that determines, that's used to help to figure out what exactly is meant specifically by affordable.

399
00:30:00,708 --> 00:30:04,430
So often people will ask, affordable, what does that mean in terms of numbers?

400
00:30:05,110 --> 00:30:07,532
So there's this formula that can be applied to figure that out.

401
00:30:08,953 --> 00:30:11,856
13,000 square feet of a grocery store.

402
00:30:12,137 --> 00:30:13,759
That's another aim of this project.

403
00:30:13,799 --> 00:30:20,106
So they want to build a small grocery store, community grocery store, to connect with this housing structure.

404
00:30:20,967 --> 00:30:22,890
You can see it labeled New Grocer on the map.

405
00:30:24,156 --> 00:30:28,001
There'd be a cafe as well across from that attached to that residential building.

406
00:30:28,261 --> 00:30:29,322
It's labeled New Cafe.

407
00:30:30,403 --> 00:30:31,885
The other thing is they would build a garage.

408
00:30:32,566 --> 00:30:38,112
You can see it labeled New Garage in the corner close by City Hall.

409
00:30:38,132 --> 00:30:41,696
There was some concern because obviously this project is very close to the senior center.

410
00:30:43,438 --> 00:30:44,879
you know, with senior parking.

411
00:30:45,239 --> 00:30:52,583
And I believe the developer mentioned at one of the meetings that we'll be parking close to the senior center for seniors to alleviate those concerns.

412
00:30:52,623 --> 00:30:58,727
But some were wondering, you know, well, if the seniors have to go to the garage, that's a long walk to get to the senior center.

413
00:30:58,747 --> 00:31:02,169
You can see where the garage is in relation to that senior center.

414
00:31:02,749 --> 00:31:03,730
That's not going to work, Nick.

415
00:31:04,838 --> 00:31:16,000
Um, so connecting this back to zoning the zoning, um, in addition to passing this Medford Square district, uh, about a week before that, the city council passed is zoning

416
00:31:16,718 --> 00:31:38,546
Amendment to create a overlay district or special zoning district just for transom So this is zoning specifically for transom and a number of elected officials Admitted including director hunt that this is to you know Economically benefit the developer and to make sure that developers project gets through as easily as possible

417
00:31:39,586 --> 00:31:43,049
So they created this special zoning overlay district.

418
00:31:43,429 --> 00:31:46,051
I was personally concerned legally with spot zoning.

419
00:31:46,851 --> 00:31:56,158
Spot zoning, for anyone who isn't aware, it's when you zone basically for the economic development or benefit of a developer and not for the greater community purpose.

420
00:31:56,358 --> 00:32:00,801
So I had requested that the council solicit a legal opinion on spot zoning.

421
00:32:01,482 --> 00:32:03,563
Ultimately, they chose not to do that.

422
00:32:03,823 --> 00:32:05,665
And of course, we don't have a city solicitor.

423
00:32:06,185 --> 00:32:08,266
Yeah, we could have got that opinion from the solicitor.

424
00:32:08,286 --> 00:32:09,046
That's pretty sad.

425
00:32:09,106 --> 00:32:10,607
Instead it has to come from K.P.

426
00:32:10,687 --> 00:32:10,927
Law.

427
00:32:11,767 --> 00:32:13,568
So the council didn't want to do that, unfortunately.

428
00:32:14,068 --> 00:32:24,792
But this zoning in a nutshell basically allows for Transcend to build more units and higher and also get that off-site parking garage into their plans.

429
00:32:25,917 --> 00:32:31,985
And the whole idea of zoning is essentially, do we allow things as of right or do we require some community discretion?

430
00:32:32,846 --> 00:32:42,219
So with this zoning ordinance, it's basically to try to eliminate that community discretion and make it so transom doesn't have to go to the community development board as much, if at all.

431
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,642
or the council or the community as a whole for its plans.

432
00:32:45,682 --> 00:32:47,263
Well, that's plain wrong.

433
00:32:47,784 --> 00:32:48,664
I'm just a host here.

434
00:32:48,704 --> 00:32:49,645
I just ask questions.

